```xml
<output>
<analysis>
<has-cmf>The post does not contain a CMF number. While the absence of a CMF number is not automatically disqualifying, it suggests the post might not be directly linked to an official campaign.</has-cmf>
<refers-to-candidate>The post refers to the PSD (Partidul Social Democrat) by name and implicitly promotes voting for them.  While it doesn't name a specific candidate, the context strongly suggests an endorsement of the party and its candidates in the Vrancea County area. This fulfills "Article 36 (7) - a".</refers-to-candidate>
<addresses-the-wide-population>The post is a paid advertisement on Facebook, a public platform, targeting Vrancea County. This clearly addresses a wide population and is not a private communication. This fulfills "Article 36 (7) - c".</addresses-the-wide-population>
<electoral-objective>The primary objective of the post is to encourage voters in Vrancea County to vote for the PSD on December 1st. The call to action ("Te așteptăm pe 1 decembrie la vot!") directly aims to influence voting behavior. This fulfills "Article 36 (7) - c".</electoral-objective>
<journalism>The post does not present information in a journalistic manner. It lacks objectivity and is clearly promotional in nature, aiming to persuade voters rather than inform them. It does not meet the standards of journalistic reporting.</journalism>
<personal_opinion>The post does not express a personal opinion; it's a direct appeal for votes for the PSD.  It's not a personal expression but a political advertisement.</personal_opinion>
</analysis>

<conclusion>
<post_id>1723851535114433</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
The Facebook post, paid for by PSD Vrancea, is a clear form of electoral propaganda.  It directly encourages voters to vote for the PSD, fulfilling all criteria of Article 36 (7) of LEGE nr. 334 din 17 iulie 2006. The post's timing (after the official campaign period, according to the provided `end_date`), its targeting of a specific geographical area (Vrancea County), and its explicit call to action ("Te așteptăm pe 1 decembrie la vot!") strongly suggest an intention to influence the election results.  The fact that it's a paid advertisement further strengthens this conclusion.  While it doesn't mention specific candidates, the association with the PSD is undeniable and the impact is clearly positive for the party.  The absence of a CMF number, while not definitive, adds to the suspicion of potential non-compliance.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>TRUE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
<electoral-propaganda-candidates>
  <candidate><name>Partidul Social Democrat (PSD)</name><impact>POSITIVE</impact></candidate>
</electoral-propaganda-candidates>
<responsible-party-or-group>PSD</responsible-party-or-group>
<message-for-police>
Partidul Social Democrat - Filiala Vrancea, pentru încălcarea articolului 98 t) din LEGEA nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015, prin publicarea unei postări plătite pe Facebook după ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024 (ID postare: 1723851535114433), cu mesajul explicit „Te așteptăm pe 1 decembrie la vot!”,  care îndeamnă la vot pentru Partidul Social Democrat, având un efect electoral pozitiv pentru PSD. Postarea, cu o cheltuială de 900-999 RON, a atins 40.000-45.000 de impresii, vizând populația din județul Vrancea, constituie propagandă electorală interzisă după încheierea perioadei legale de campanie.  Contact: vrancea@psd.ro, +40749034652, https://psd.ro/.  Această postare încalcă prevederile legale privind continuarea propagandei electorale după încheierea acesteia, influențând votul alegătorilor.
</message-for-police>
</conclusion>
</output>
```
